                In 2009, Ronaldo transferred to Real Madrid for a then-world record fee, where he became the club's all-time leading scorer and won four more Champions League titles. In 2018, he moved to Juventus in Italy, continuing his success by winning two Serie A titles. Ronaldo is known for his incredible goal-scoring ability, athleticism, and versatility on the field. He has won five Ballon d'Or awards, recognizing him as the best player in the world. Off the field, Ronaldo is also known for his philanthropy and business ventures, including his CR7 brand.


